    {
      "id": 83,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        -1259.9163905578614,
        1032.207800744627
      ],
      "size": [
        510,
        680
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 15,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "Incremental changes described here",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Workflow 4: ModelSampling Proxy\n\n### What Changed\n\n**ModelSamplingAuraFlow_ZIMG** is now connected. It receives the MODEL from the host UNETLoader and patches its sampling configuration.\n\nThis node calls `model.clone()` and `model.add_object_patch()` on the model — operations that modify model internals. The MODEL object is a `ModelPatcher`, ComfyUI’s heaviest framework type.\n\n### What Crosses the Process Boundary\n\n**MODEL (ModelPatcher)** — as a proxy reference, plus **ModelSampling** config objects that the child patches onto the model.\n\nThe child receives a `ModelPatcherProxy`. When it calls `model.clone()`, that call goes via RPC to the host, which clones the real model and returns a new proxy reference.\n\n### Proxy Complexity\n\nModelPatcher is the most complex proxy in the system:\n\n- `clone()` → host clones, returns new ref\n- `add_object_patch()` → host applies patch\n- VRAM management → host handles allocation\n- Weight access → host-side only\n\nThe sampling config (`ModelSamplingAdvanced`) is serialized as data and sent to the host, where it’s applied to the real model.\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
